                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-180-victim1225 t18170917-180-viclabel918"></join>, <placeName id="t18170917-180-crimeloc919">Coleman-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-180-crimeloc919" type="placeName" value="Coleman-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-180-crimeloc919" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-180-off916 t18170917-180-crimeloc919"></join>; the prisoner was his <rs id="t18170917-180-deflabel920" type="occupation">labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-180-defend1223 t18170917-180-deflabel920"></join>; having often lost property, I searched the premises every night when the men left work. On the 18th of July, I found a bag of smalts in a dark corner in the cellar, I let it remain there, and placed myself to watch till eight o'clock, when every body had left except the prisoner, in whom the greatest confidence was placed - He slept on the premises; I left the place, and went about fifty yards beyond the gate, and waited about a quarter of an hour; the prisoner came out with a parcel under his apron - I took him and found it was the smalts I had seen in the cellar. I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I meant to pay for them.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18170917-180-verdict921" type="verdictDescription">
